abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump will hold back-to-back meetings with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Israeli opposition leader Benny Gantz on Monday as he prepares to release his long-delayed Middle East peace plan.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump will hold back-to-back meetings with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Israeli opposition leader Benny Gantz on Monday as he prepares to release his long-delayed Middle East peace plan.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump will hold back-to-back meetings with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Israeli opposition leader Benny Gantz on Monday as he prepares to release his long-delayed Middle East peace plan.
headline_main: Trump to Meet With Netanyahu and Gantz as He Readies Mideast Peace Plan
headline_print_headline: Trump to Meet With Netanyahu and Gantz as He Readies Mideast Peace Plan

abstract: The former vice president hasn’t been a favorite of editorial boards, and lost out on the coveted Des Moines Register endorsement. But The Sioux City Journal backed his candidacy.
snippet: The former vice president hasn’t been a favorite of editorial boards, and lost out on the coveted Des Moines Register endorsement. But The Sioux City Journal backed his candidacy.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has not been a favorite of newspaper editorial boards so far, and he lost out on the coveted Des Moines Register endorsement on Saturday. But his campaign emerged from the day with a different endorsement to trumpet, from The Sioux City Journal in northwest Iowa.
headline_main: Biden picks up a helpful (and rare) newspaper endorsement.

abstract: In an extraordinary back-and-forth between a president and a congressman, President Trump warned that Representative Adam Schiff, the lead House impeachment manager, “has not paid the price, yet.”
snippet: In an extraordinary back-and-forth between a president and a congressman, President Trump warned that Representative Adam Schiff, the lead House impeachment manager, “has not paid the price, yet.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Adam B. Schiff, the House’s lead impeachment manager, accused President Trump on Sunday of trying to threaten him on Twitter and urged Republican senators to find the “moral courage to stand up” to a “wrathful and vindictive president.”

abstract: Once heralded as the next Nike, the sportswear giant has been hurt by slumping sales and unflattering revelations about its corporate culture.
snippet: Once heralded as the next Nike, the sportswear giant has been hurt by slumping sales and unflattering revelations about its corporate culture.
lead_paragraph: In the summer of 2018, two top Under Armour executives traveled to the West Coast on a critical mission. Kevin Plank, the sports apparel company’s founder and chief executive, and Patrik Frisk, its president and chief operating officer, needed to persuade Stephen Curry, the Golden State Warriors star and the company’s highest-profile endorser, not to leave the brand.

abstract: President Donald Trump's impeachment trial enters a pivotal week as his defense team resumes its case and senators face a critical vote on whether to hear witnesses or proceed directly to a vote that is widely expected to end in his acquittal. The articles of impeachment charge Trump with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.
snippet: President Donald Trump's impeachment trial enters a pivotal week as his defense team resumes its case and senators face a critical vote on whether to hear witnesses or proceed directly to a vote that is widely expected to end in his acquittal. The...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump's impeachment trial enters a pivotal week as his defense team resumes its case and senators face a critical vote on whether to hear witnesses or proceed directly to a vote that is widely expected to end in his acquittal. The articles of impeachment charge Trump with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.
headline_main: Defense Resumes in Key Impeachment Week; Dems Seek Witnesses
headline_print_headline: Defense Resumes in Key Impeachment Week; Dems Seek Witnesses

abstract: A coveted Iowa surrogate says he called Pete Buttigieg the “next president” because that’s just something you say when someone visits the state. “It’s a courtesy,” he said.
snippet: A coveted Iowa surrogate says he called Pete Buttigieg the “next president” because that’s just something you say when someone visits the state. “It’s a courtesy,” he said.
lead_paragraph: STORM LAKE, Iowa — Pete Buttigieg had one of northwest Iowa’s most coveted surrogates introduce him before a town-hall-style event Saturday night at Buena Vista University: David Johnson, a former state senator who in 2016 quit the Republican Party when Donald J. Trump won its presidential nomination.
headline_main: A Klobuchar endorser switches to Buttigieg? Not quite.

abstract: The Vermont senator returned to the campaign trail, with Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and Michael Moore in tow.
snippet: The Vermont senator returned to the campaign trail, with Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and Michael Moore in tow.
lead_paragraph: AMES, Iowa — The impeachment trial scrambled plans for the senators competing in the Democratic primary race. They would normally be blitzing Iowa in the final days before the caucuses, but they instead spent much of the past week in Washington, serving as jurors for the trial of President Trump, before returning to Iowa on Saturday.
headline_main: Sanders returns to Iowa: ‘I am really delighted to be here.’

abstract: Elizabeth Warren received the coveted endorsement from Iowa’s largest paper.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren received the coveted endorsement from Iowa’s largest paper.
lead_paragraph: MUSCATINE, Iowa — The Des Moines Register endorsed Senator Elizabeth Warren for the Democratic presidential nomination on Saturday night, calling her “the best leader for these times.”
headline_main: How Warren found out she won the Des Moines Register endorsement.

abstract: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders and former Vice President Joe Biden appear locked in a tight race for the Democratic presidential nomination, as both campaigned in Iowa on Sunday with only days left until the first contest.
snippet: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders and former Vice President Joe Biden appear locked in a tight race for the Democratic presidential nomination, as both campaigned in Iowa on Sunday with only days left until the first contest.
lead_paragraph: FORT DODGE, Iowa — U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders and former Vice President Joe Biden appear locked in a tight race for the Democratic presidential nomination, as both campaigned in Iowa on Sunday with only days left until the first contest.
headline_main: U.S. Presidential Hopefuls Sanders, Biden in Tight Race in Early Primary States
headline_print_headline: U.S. Presidential Hopefuls Sanders, Biden in Tight Race in Early Primary States
